    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>What about using a <code>.yourapp</code> directory under <code>user.home</code> instead? You shouldn't face any permission problem, a windows user won't really notice it, it would be hidden on GNU/Linux. </p>\n\n<p>For temporary stuff, you may prefer <code>java.io.tmpdir</code> but keep in mind that the content of this directory (<code>/tmp</code> on GNU/Linux) might be wiped out upon reboot (e.g. with Debian distros). So this is really for temporary stuff.</p>\n\n<p>PS: I prefer to use <code>File.separator</code> over <code>System.getProperty(\"file.separator\")</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 20189,
      "reputation" : 170737,
      "user_id" : 48015,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b722a5f7d2d809629ee40c63cc8576b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Christoph",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/48015/christoph"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1762385380,
    "last_edit_date" : 1762385380,
    "creation_date" : 1259108317,
    "answer_id" : 1793896,
    "question_id" : 1793856,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>user.dir</code> is the current working directory; use <code>user.home</code> instead and <code>java.io.tmpdir</code> for temporary files.</p>\n<p>Here's the <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#getProperties%28%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">list of predefined properties</a> for Java 1.5, and for <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/System.html#getProperties()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java 25</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
